1
00:00:21,640 --> 00:00:23,720
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

2
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:33,239
Hello. Welcome to Top Gear.

3
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:34,479
In tonight's show,

4
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,719
we've got every sort of car
you can imagine.

5
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:38,399
We're rammed to the gills
with 'em.

6
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:39,959
We've got dirt-cheap cars.

7
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:41,519
We've got Italian supercars.

8
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,839
We've got electric cars.
We've got pick-up trucks.

9
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:45,479
And, ladies and gentlemen,

10
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:49,319
we've also got
a Vauxhall Agila!

11
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:51,719
Rrrrr-reee!
Agila! Agila!

12
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:53,839
Whatever your tastes,
whatever your budget,

13
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:55,679
we've got something for you
tonight.

14
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:58,119
But we're kicking off with one of
the greatest names

15
00:00:58,120 --> 00:00:59,480
in motoring.

16
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:04,160
Maserati.

17
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:12,879
The Italian sports car company with
a truly glorious history.

18
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:15,919
COMMENTATOR: Stirling Moss in his
Maserati number 7 wins the race.

19
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:18,479
There at the very
dawn of Formula 1,

20
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:22,319
this was the team that took the
great Juan Manuel Fangio

21
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:24,639
to his final F1 title

22
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:26,399
and went on to build

23
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:30,159
some of the most beautiful
race cars, and road cars,

24
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:32,080
ever seen.

25
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:38,039
But in recent times,

26
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:41,919
the shine has faded
on the old trident badge.

27
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:44,519
Yes, there have been
some decent saloons

28
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,479
and pretty coupes,

29
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:49,719
but the closest Maserati has
come to a real head-turner

30
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:52,319
was 2004's MC12,

31
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,920
which was just a Ferrari Enzo
with a body kit.

32
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:03,919
For the last genuine
Maserati supercar

33
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,720
you've got
to go back to this...

34
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:10,000
..the beautiful Bora.

35
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:19,639
This was the last genuine
Maserati supercar,

36
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:22,440
and it was built in 1971.

37
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:29,720
So we haven't had a new one
in over 50 years.

38
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,920
Must be time for a new one,
then.

39
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,199
This is the all-new

40
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:47,879
Maserati MC20.

41
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:49,640
It's got supercar looks.

42
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,440
It's got supercar doors.

43
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,879
And with prices
starting at Â£190,000,

44
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:00,840
it's got a proper
supercar price tag.

45
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:17,519
But after 50 years
out of the game,

46
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:22,159
what sort of a supercar
has Maserati built?

47
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,639
You might think

48
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:27,359
if you were building a
supercar from scratch

49
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:29,679
fit for the third decade
of the 21st century

50
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:33,799
that you'd go for some electric
hybrid plug-in thingy.

51
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:38,079
But the MC20 is at heart
quite old school.

52
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:40,959
No e-motor,
no regenerative braking,

53
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:44,519
just a turbo-charged V6
behind me

54
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:47,120
sending power
to the rear wheels.

55
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:57,520
That turbo-charged V6
makes 621 horsepower...

56
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:02,479
..which, in a car that weighs
just under 1,500 kilos,

57
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:04,160
is plenty.

58
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:13,160
It'll do 0-60 in 2.9 seconds...

59
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,239
..and over 200mph flat out.

60
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:21,759
By any standards,
it's a very fast car!

61
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:25,920
You're not going to be late
for anything.

62
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:37,040
So, it definitely does the
whole supercar speed thing...

63
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:42,599
..but with a super-stiff
carbon-fibre tub,

64
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:45,719
and double wishbone
suspension all round,

65
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:48,159
where the MC20
really comes to life...

66
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,920
..is through the corners.

67
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:56,599
This chassis can handle
really rapid direction changes.

68
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:59,239
Wind the lock on, it's so fast

69
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,759
it darts around in a way
that no Porsche 911

70
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:04,399
could possibly hope to do.

71
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:06,079
You've got to be
on top of your game.

72
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,200
That's the way it should be.

73
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:11,959
Good front-end grip. The back wants
to come round,

74
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:13,360
but it's nicely balanced.

75
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:28,080
This is, really, a massive
620-horsepower go-kart!

76
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:38,399
Issues?
Well, it's an Italian supercar.

77
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,799
Of course there are issues.

78
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:45,359
The brakes - they're effective,
but they take a huge push.

79
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:49,999
The pedal requires much, much more
effort than any rival car.

80
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,959
Maserati's done this
deliberately to give it

81
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,280
a kind of race-car feel.

82
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,919
But the steering is so light
there's a bit of a mismatch

83
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,519
between the input required
for the brake

84
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:02,119
and the little delicate
steering inputs required

85
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,479
for the light steering.

86
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:06,199
I think the biggest problem
is the size of the fuel tank -

87
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,079
60 litres.

88
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:10,320
And this V6 likes a drink.

89
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:13,239
And then there's the question

90
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:16,760
of where on earth you're actually
going to put anything.

91
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,439
Now, normally, when your engine's in
the rear,

92
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,600
you have lots of luggage
space up front.

93
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,319
Ah.

94
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:29,279
About enough room
for a pair of undercrackers

95
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,679
and maybe a sock.

96
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:33,399
However, there is more
boot space back here.

97
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:36,279
The trouble is,
it's right next to the engine,

98
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:39,039
which means it gets quite hot
- bad news

99
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,279
if you're transporting
ice cream,

100
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:42,519
very good news

101
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:46,440
if you're a high-speed
pizza delivery service.

102
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,440
Argh, that's hot!

103
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:53,479
But look,

104
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:57,999
it wouldn't be a Maserati
without a few...foibles.

105
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,239
And in truth, it's just good
to have that badge

106
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:04,279
back in the supercar game.

107
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:09,159
Would I have this MC20
over a McLaren or a Ferrari?

108
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,759
You know what? I think I would.

109
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,439
I love the simplicity.

110
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:15,319
It's not trying
to be a clever hybrid.

111
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:16,599
I love the way it looks.

112
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,199
I love the way it drives.

113
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:21,199
It's unlike anything else
on sale.

114
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:23,759
Will it provide a prosperous

115
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:26,919
and stable financial future
for Maserati?

116
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:28,719
Probably not.

117
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:31,480
But I'm so glad it exists
anyway.

118
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,479
Whoo-hoo-hooo!

119
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,560
Ha!

120
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,279
HE LAUGHS
Dip a wheel in the dirt!

121
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:41,720
Dip a wheel in the dirt!

122
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:48,080
I'll tell you what,
it's a really great car!

123
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:51,799
Welcome back, Maserati.

124
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:54,080
We have missed you!

125
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,880
