126
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:09,359
Beautiful.

127
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,439
Look at that.

128
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,679
I love it. Last week Lotus,

129
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,759
this week Maserati -

130
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:18,279
those legendary names coming back
out the woodwork

131
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,079
and absolutely smashing it.

132
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,119
You wouldn't put your money
on it. This is Maserati,

133
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,839
and its track record
isn't great. When they say,

134
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:26,959
"We're gonna make
a carbon-fibre supercar

135
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:28,919
"from scratch,
including the engine,"

136
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,879
the correct answer is,
"Course you are, lads."

137
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:31,919
LAUGHTER

138
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,839
But actually, they've gone
and done it.

139
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,079
And it's good. And I believe
there's an electric version

140
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:38,879
in the pipeline. Is there, Pad?
Yeah, they're saying

141
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:40,919
there's a convertible and an
electric version

142
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:41,879
in a couple of years.

143
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:44,239
However, this is Maserati.
A couple of years could mean

144
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,799
four or five
financial implosions,

145
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:48,959
so we won't hold our breath!
But this is still a great car.

146
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:52,999
Well, now it's time to find out
just how fast the MC20 is

147
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:57,240
by putting it round our track
in the hands of...The Stig.

148
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,799
CHRIS: Here we go. The MC20, looking
menacing in black,

149
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,360
our test track looking
almost entirely under water.

150
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:10,360
The car stepping out of line at
100mph there on the straight.

151
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,720
Look at the standing water.

152
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,839
The MC20's carbon-fibre tub

153
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:26,239
made by the legendary
Italian race outfit Dallara.

154
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,520
This car is built
of the good stuff.

155
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,239
Stig working his way through
that eight-speed

156
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,039
double-clutch gearbox.

157
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:38,560
ENGINE HUMS

158
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:42,760
That V6, not the most exciting
sounding.

159
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:48,720
Into the Follow Through.
This could be interesting.

160
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:54,040
Stig getting his money out
of that steering wheel today.

161
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,720
Holding it together there.

162
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:10,439
And across the line.

163
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:13,040
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

164
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,240
All right.

165
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:22,359
Straight away, off the bat,
it was a very, very wet lap -

166
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:27,199
tipping it down. So...
Yeah? The time was rock bottom.

167
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,159
1:30.4.

168
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:32,399
Ah. And not a good tyre
in the wet either. No, no.

169
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,999
So, when it dried out,

170
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,039
and just after
the cameras had left...

171
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,199
Oh.

172
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:39,039
..we sent The Stig out again.

173
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:41,479
On a dry lap,
what do you reckon?

174
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:45,199
So, 1:30.4 on a wet lap.

175
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,799
17 dead.

176
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:51,079
17? Ooh... Ooh. So we're down here.
Yeah. Ooh.

177
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,679
1:20. Higher.

178
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:53,999
Higher.

179
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,439
I reckon... Higher.

180
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,679
About there. About...
Where are you thinking?

181
00:10:57,680 --> 00:11:00,879
A bit slower than the GTS
AMG. Behind the Bugatti?

182
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:03,039
Not a million miles away.
Yeah?

183
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,479
1:16.6.

184
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,799
Oh.

185
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:09,039
It's faster than a Veyron SS!

186
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:11,400
APPLAUSE
Faster than a Veyron SS.

187
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,519
Look at that.

188
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:15,599
Unbelievable.

189
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:18,999
And now it's time to move on
and talk about money saving.

190
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,159
Correct,
because we've all noticed

191
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:24,199
everything's getting very expensive
right now in the UK,

192
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,799
including cars.

193
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:28,599
In the last year, the average
price of a second-hand car

194
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:31,319
has gone up by five grand.
Wow.

195
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,559
But are there still
cheap, cheerful, reliable

196
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:35,479
used-car bargains to be had?

197
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,480
We decided to find out.

198
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:49,079
To see if you can still pick up a
dependable runabout

199
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:52,879
for not a lot of cash,
the producers had rounded up

200
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:55,400
a load of used cars
for us to have a look at...

201
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,159
..all bought for less
than 500 quid,

202
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:02,239
all with MOTs, ready to roll...

203
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,720
..in theory.

204
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:10,439
Wow. Well, I've got to say!

205
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:13,519
Do you know what?
Looking round already...

206
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:16,639
How are they this cheap?
Bargains!

207
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:19,639
They can't have
MOTs, can they?

208
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,000
Oh. Challenge.

209
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:23,959
250 quid.

210
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:26,719
What, this? Yeah. These are great
cars, tough as you like.

211
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,839
Here you are.
Yeah.

212
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:31,279
"You have five minutes
to each choose a car."

213
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:35,599
"You may start the engine but you
may not move the car.

214
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,519
"Whichever car you're in
when the time's up" - oh! -

215
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,679
"is the one you're going
to be driving."

216
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:41,959
When does the five minutes start?

217
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,639
Don't know.
HORN HONKS

218
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:46,479
Oh, there it is. Ay-oh-ay!
Right, I've seen that.

219
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,719
First things first,

220
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:50,039
rear suspension
I think's the problem.

221
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:51,679
That's quite solid.

222
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:54,159
This is the one that young Paddy
would have bought,

223
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:55,959
cos I'd have been skint

224
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:58,160
and I'd have known it'd run
and run and run.

225
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:01,279
ENGINE RUNS

226
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,679
Not too bad, that. I'll put
that in the old reserves.

227
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:05,479
HE LAUGHS

228
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,519
What's in there, Chris?

229
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,799
Air. Lots of fresh air!

230
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,279
Paddy, what do you reckon?

231
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,319
A bit of headroom for you!

232
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:14,199
Practical.

233
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,319
ENGINE RUNS

234
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:19,440
No. Can't do it.

235
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,079
There's a little MX-5 here!

236
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:27,039
Have you seen the
rust on that thing, Paddy?

237
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:30,359
Rust? Oh, it's just a bit of...

238
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:32,399
Oh...

239
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:34,279
Oh, dear.

240
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:36,359
That's not good.

241
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:38,479
For 500 quid,
the Merc's got to be

242
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,239
the one that appeals,
hasn't it?

243
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:42,279
She's done 380,000
kilometres.

244
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:44,319
ENGINE RUNS

245
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,999
Starts OK.

246
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,319
That is a good car.

247
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,359
Oh, I'm going to look
at the MG.

248
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,919
I'm panic...panicking.

249
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:55,199
Lads, 364! It's got the chequered
flag on and everything!

250
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,119
Start it up, Pad.

251
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:59,159
ENGINE RUNS

252
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:02,839
Absolutely sweet as a nut,
this one.

253
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:06,599
Oh-ho. No, out of that one.
Diesel.

